moves.1. e4: This a good game with a lot of threats from both sides, most of them not obvious.
moves.1... e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Bc4 Nc6 4. d3 Bc5: The black bishop was preventing his castling, so Qxf4 was quite a big threat
moves.10. Nd5 Qg6: However since the bishop could easily be defend with a counter attack that was a mistake
moves.14... Bxg4 15. Bxf7+ Kxf7 16. Nxd6+ Bxd6: White was perhaps trying to castle queens side but Rf1 was a better move
moves.17... Rf8 18. Bxh6: This was intent at getting the rook at f8 but this move was poorly calculated
moves.18... Bg3+: Forcing the king to be in line with the rook
moves.20. Kg1 Bf2+: The only move was Qxf3 because h2 was leading to mate. And people don't like to play without a queen
